SUMMARY:David Attenborough: A Life on Our Planet
DESCRIPTION:Even if you don’t recognise his name\, you definitely recognise his voice. \nDavid Attenborough recently celebrated his 100th birthday. Over a career spanning several decades\, he brought the wonders of the natural world into living rooms across the globe: starting with observation and moving towards advocacy. Series such as Planet Earth and Blue Planet made him one of the most influential figures in natural history. \nThough revered by many\, his legacy is a subject of critical debate. From the framing of his subjects to the narrative around conservation\, he has lived and broadcasted through multiple changing narratives around nature. How far is his influence? What is his responsibility? \nIn this session\, Theodore Baskaran and Kartik Shanker\, with Kalyan Varma as moderator\, discuss Sir David Attenborough’s life and work. The session will conclude with an audience Q&A. \nThis event is a part of the Environment Day programming at BIC. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/david-attenborough-a-life-on-our-planet/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Environment,Film,Science
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thumbnail_DA_ALOOP2.jpg
END:VEVENT
