SUMMARY:Planting Forests in Small Spaces
DESCRIPTION:You do not need to be told climate change is real. You already feel the impact\, the consequence\, in your daily life. \nBut as an average citizen\, what can you do? \nThis panel discusses decades of measurable\, on-ground impact: over 400 microforests restored across India using the Miyawaki technique\, living Green Walls for industrial parks\, and Nature Labs that put children in direct contact with the natural world. The conversation will open to audience questions. \nThis session is not a lecture. It is a Call-To-Action. \nThis event is a part of the Environment Day programming at BIC. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/planting-forests-in-small-spaces/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Environment,Technology
